@startuml
!define RECTANGLE class

participant "User" as User
participant "Browser" as Browser
participant "AppHeader\nComponent" as AppHeader
participant "ProductCard\nComponent" as ProductCard
participant "Next.js\nPage" as Page
participant "Redux Store\n(cart.slice)" as Redux
participant "Next.js\nAPI Routes" as API
participant "clicks.service.js" as ClickService
participant "DataStax Driver" as Driver
database "DSE/Cassandra\nDatabase" as Database

== User Authentication Flow ==
User -> Browser: Access application
Browser -> Page: Load page
Page -> API: GET /api/auth/[...nextauth]
API -> API: NextAuth processes authentication
API --> Page: Return auth session
Page -> AppHeader: Render with auth state
AppHeader --> User: Show sign-in/sign-out option

User -> AppHeader: Click sign-in
AppHeader -> API: POST /api/auth/[...nextauth]
API -> API: Create simplified customer ID
API --> AppHeader: Return session with customer ID
AppHeader --> User: Display signed-in state

== Page Browsing Tracking Flow ==
User -> Browser: Navigate to category page
Browser -> Page: GET /category/[category]
activate Page
Page -> Page: getServerSideProps() executes
Page -> ClickService: trackPageBrowsing(customerId, category)
activate ClickService
ClickService -> ClickService: Check environment variables
ClickService -> Driver: Connect to database
activate Driver
Driver -> Database: Establish connection
Database --> Driver: Connection established
Driver --> ClickService: Client ready
ClickService -> Driver: Execute INSERT query
Driver -> Database: INSERT INTO clickstream\n(customer_id, page, timestamp)
Database --> Driver: Acknowledgment
Driver --> ClickService: Query result
deactivate Driver
ClickService --> Page: Tracking complete
deactivate ClickService
Page -> API: GET /api/products/[category]
API -> API: Filter products by category
API --> Page: Return product data
Page --> Browser: Render category page with products
deactivate Page
Browser --> User: Display category page

== Add to Cart Flow ==
User -> ProductCard: Click "Add to Cart"
ProductCard -> Redux: dispatch(addToCart(product))
activate Redux
Redux -> Redux: Update cart state
Redux -> API: POST /api/products (node-fetch)
activate API
API -> API: Parse request body
API -> ClickService: addToCart(customerId, productId, timestamp)
activate ClickService
ClickService -> Driver: Connect to database
activate Driver
Driver -> Database: Establish connection
Database --> Driver: Connection established
Driver --> ClickService: Client ready
ClickService -> Driver: Execute INSERT query
Driver -> Database: INSERT INTO clickstream\n(customer_id, product_id,\nadd_to_cart_timestamp)
Database --> Driver: Acknowledgment
Driver --> ClickService: Query result
deactivate Driver
ClickService --> API: Insert complete
deactivate ClickService
API --> Redux: Success response
deactivate API
Redux --> ProductCard: Cart updated
deactivate Redux
ProductCard --> User: Update cart badge

== View Cart Flow ==
User -> AppHeader: Click cart icon
AppHeader -> Browser: Navigate to /cart
Browser -> Page: Load cart page
Page -> Redux: Select cart state
Redux --> Page: Return cart items
Page --> Browser: Render cart with items
Browser --> User: Display cart contents

== View Clickstream History Flow ==
User -> Browser: Navigate to /history
Browser -> Page: GET /history
activate Page
Page -> Page: getServerSideProps() executes
Page -> API: GET /api/history?customerId=[id]
activate API
API -> ClickService: getActivity(customerId)
activate ClickService
ClickService -> Driver: Connect to database
activate Driver
Driver -> Database: Establish connection
Database --> Driver: Connection established
Driver --> ClickService: Client ready
ClickService -> Driver: Execute SELECT query
Driver -> Database: SELECT * FROM clickstream\nWHERE customer_id = ?
Database --> Driver: Return rows
Driver --> ClickService: Query results
deactivate Driver
ClickService --> API: Return activity data
deactivate ClickService
API --> Page: Return clickstream history
deactivate API
Page --> Browser: Render history page
deactivate Page
Browser --> User: Display clickstream events

@enduml
